article.headline: Hannah Stuelke scores 16 points and No. 22 Iowa women defeat BYU 68-48 at Cancun Challenge
article.description: — Hannah Stuelke had 16 points and eight rebounds to lead No. 22 Iowa to a 68-48 victory over BYU at the Cancun Challenge on Friday night.
article.linkText: Hannah Stuelke scores 16 points and No. 22 Iowa women defeat BYU 68-48 at Cancun Challenge
article.story: CANCUN, Mexico -- — Hannah Stuelke had 16 points and eight rebounds to lead No. 22 Iowa to a 68-48 victory over BYU at the Cancun Challenge on Friday night. The Hawkeyes led just 25-19 at halftime before posting 43 points in the second half. Addison O'Grady scored four points and the Hawkeyes added two 3-pointers in a 10-3 run early in the third quarter, building a 35-22 lead with six minutes remaining in the period. Iowa went on to score 20 points in the quarter and took a 45-30 lead to the fourth. O’Grady scored 12 points and Aaliyah Guyton had 11 for Iowa (8-0). Sydney Affolter had seven points, 10 rebounds, four assists and five steals. Kemery Congdon had 13 points and Amari Whiting 11 for the Cougars (6-2). The Hawkeyes led 16-10 after one quarter and maintained that six-point lead in the second quarter despite managing only nine points. Iowa led 25-19 at halftime with Stuelke leading the way with 11 points. Lucy Olsen, Iowa's leading scorer at 17.3 points per game, missed her second straight game with a large gash on her knee. ------ Get poll alerts and updates on the AP Top 25 throughout the season.
